Class SortLevel

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gembox.spreadsheet.SortLevel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.gembox.spreadsheet.internal.styles.CellFormatDataFormatHolder

    public final class SortLevel
extends Object
implements com.gembox.spreadsheet.internal.styles.CellFormatDataFormatHolder
    Represents sort settings for a single sort level.

    Following methods shows various ways to specify and apply a SortState to a range of cells. 

    
public static void sort1(ExcelWorksheet worksheet) {
    // Specify and apply Sort using less-verbose, fluent, but less understandable interface.
    worksheet.getCells().getSubrange("A1", "D20").sort(true).
        by(0).
        by(1, true).
        by(2, "Female", "Male").
        apply();
}

public static void sort2(ExcelWorksheet worksheet) {
    // Specify and apply Sort using more verbose, but more understandable interface.
    SortState sort = worksheet.getCells().getSubrange("A1", "D20").sort(true);

    sort.getLevels().add(0);

    SortLevel level2 = sort.getLevels().add(1);
    level2.setDescending(true);

    SortLevel level3 = sort.getLevels().add(2);
    level3.setCustomList("Female", "Male");

    sort.apply();
}

        public int getColumnRowIndex()

        Gets the column (or the row, if SortState.isLeftToRight() is true) index relative to the range that this sort level applies to.

        Value is equal to or greater than zero and less than width (or height, if SortState.isLeftToRight() is true) of the range.

        Returns:
        The column (or the row, if SortState.isLeftToRight() is true) index relative to the range that this sort level applies to.

      • getComparator

        public Comparator<ExcelCell> getComparator()

        Gets the comparison method that compares two ExcelCells.

        Default value is default comparison method based on the settings of this sort level.

        This member is not loaded from and saved to XLSX file since it is not supported by Office Open XML specification. It is used to customize GemBox.Spreadsheet functionality.

        Returns:
        The comparison method that compares two ExcelCells.

      • getCustomList

        public List<String> getCustomList()

        Returns:

      • isDescending

        public boolean isDescending()

        Gets a value indicating whether to sort the values in the descending order.

        Default value is false.

        Returns:
        true to sort the values in the descending order; otherwise, false.

      • setColumnRowIndex

        public void setColumnRowIndex(int value)

        Sets the column (or the row, if SortState.isLeftToRight() is true) index relative to the range that this sort level applies to.

        Value is equal to or greater than zero and less than width (or height, if SortState.isLeftToRight() is true) of the range.

        Parameters:
        value - The column (or the row, if SortState.isLeftToRight() is true) index relative to the range that this sort level applies to.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - Sort level is removed from the sort state.
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - Value is less than zero or is equal to or greater than width (or height, if SortState.isLeftToRight() is true) of the range.
        IllegalArgumentException - Column/row at the specified index is being sorted by the same criteria more than once. Delete the duplicate sort criteria and try again.

      • setComparator

        public void setComparator(Comparator<ExcelCell> value)

        Sets the comparison method that compares two ExcelCells.

        Default value is default comparison method based on the settings of this sort level.

        Use this method to override default comparison method based on the settings of this sort level.

        This member is not loaded from and saved to XLSX file since it is not supported by Office Open XML specification. It is used to customize GemBox.Spreadsheet functionality.

        If set to null, reverts to default comparison method based on the settings of this sort level.

        Parameters:
        value - The comparison method that compares two ExcelCells.
